<h3>Toolbar:</h3>

The standard items on the toolbar generated by a
<a href="/&AGENT:name;">&AGENT:name;</a> agent include:
<dl compact>
  <dt> [X]
  <dd> -&gt; <a href="&agentPath;&agentName;/hide">&agentPath;&agentName;/hide?hide=true</a>
       <br>hides the agent's toolbar.
  <dd> -&gt; <a href="&agentPath&agentName;/help">&agentPath;&agentName;/help</a>,
       the help page
  <dt> [~]
  <dd>  -&gt; <a href="/~/">/~/</a>, your personal PIA data directory.
</dl>

<if><agent-running name=History>
    <then><p>
	You should also
	see the <a href="/History">History agent's home page</a> for more
	information about the portion of the toolbar that starts out
	``[<a href="/History">Hist</a>...''
</if>


